Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{700%g} lengthways into 2cm slices, then chop into 2cm wide chips. Pop the chips onto a large, low-sided, wide #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with @pepper{}, half the @mild paprika{1%tsp} and half the @garlic salt{1%tsp}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer. Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the chips nicely spread out.

Remove the steak from your fridge to allow it come up to room temperature. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1} and @onion{1 / 2}(peeled and thinly sliced). Halve the @bell pepper{1} and @green pepper{1}, discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Halve the @green chilli{1 / 2} lengthways (see ingredients for amount), deseed then thinly slice. Grate both types of cheese: @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}(grated) and @red leicester{60%g}(grated).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the onion and pepper, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry until soft and caramelised, ~{8-10%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Then add the @Worcester sauce{15%ml} and cook until the liquid has evaporated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove the onion and pepper mix to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Pop the now empty frying pan back on with a drizzle of oil and increase to high heat (no need to wash). When hot, then lay the @beef sizzler steaks{4} in the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, flash-fry the steaks for ~{45%seconds} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Remove the steak to a #board{} and allow to rest for ~{1-2%minutes}. Then thinly slice and cover to keep warm.

> Tip: You can use scissors to cut the steaks. IMPORTANT: The steak is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Wipe out the steak pan and pop it back on medium heat. Add the @creme fraiche{150%g} along with 1 tbsp of water per person, stir to combine then bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to low and add both the cheeses, continuously stirring until the cheese has melted and it has come together to make a creamy sauce, ~{3-4%minutes}. Take off the heat and season to taste with the remaining garlic salt and paprika.

Once everything is ready, divide the chips between your plates. Load on the onion and pepper mix, then the steak strips. Pour the cheese sauce all over, and finish with a sprinkling of green chilli (use sparingly if you don't like heat!). Tuck in and enjoy!